text: A minute of silence is what I'm asking for A minute of your time would not be too much So that today you find out that my soul is no longer dying You were absolutely wrong, don't try to go back I prefer to live a thousand years without you Than an eternity passing like this You were the love of my life And speaking clearly, I'm not going to lie to you And I don't care what you may feel This is a continuous storm It's like sinking in the sea I'm still a little absurd, fatal Why keep hurting me? chapters.headline: Struggle for Peace
chapters.summary: The speaker expresses deep emotional turmoil and a longing for peace away from toxicity, emphasizing the pain caused by a past relationship.
